GuardianEye Project Summary
===========================

Project Overview:
GuardianEye is a comprehensive student computer lab management system designed for educational environments. It provides monitoring, session control, and administrative features to manage student computer usage effectively.

Architecture:
- Multi-tier architecture with WPF clients (Admin, Client) and ASP.NET Core Server
- MVVM pattern for WPF applications
- Shared DTO architecture for consistent data transfer
- JWT-based authentication and authorization
- SQL Server/SQLite database storage

Already Implemented Features (Before Current Work):
--------------------------------------------------
✅ JWT Authentication System
   - Secure login for students and administrators
   - Role-based access control (Student/Admin)
   - Token validation and refresh mechanisms

✅ Heartbeat System
   - Real-time session validation
   - Multi-PC prevention (single active session per user)
   - Session invalidation on new login

✅ Session Enforcement
   - Automatic session timeout
   - Session counting and limits
   - Graceful session termination

✅ Hidden Developer Override System
   - Emergency access for administrators
   - Secure bypass mechanisms

✅ Admin Dashboard Foundation
   - Basic shell with navigation
   - Placeholder pages for various functions

✅ Shared DTO Architecture
   - Consistent data models between client and server
   - Login/validation/request/response DTOs

✅ Client/Server Communication
   - RESTful API endpoints
   - HTTP client services
   - JSON serialization

✅ Database Setup
   - SQLite + SQL Server support
   - Entity Framework Core
   - Database seeding (admin user)

